{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ground}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Sandslash}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ground|prevnum=027|prev=Sandshrew|nextnum=029|next=Nidoran♀|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Sandslash\n|jname=サンドパン\n|jtranslit=Sandopan\n|tmname=Sandpan\n|forme=2\n|form1=Sandslash\n|form2=Alolan Sandslash\n|image2=028Sandslash-Alola.png\n|ndex=028\n|jdex=049\n|hdex=113\n|hdex6=118\n|u2dex=114\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=098\n|adex=252\n|abrow=195\n|obrow=181\n|opbrow=011\n|type1=Ground\n|form2type1=Ice\n|form2type2=Steel\n|category=Mouse\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|height-ftin2=3\'11"\n|height-m2=1.2\n|weight-lbs=65.0\n|weight-kg=29.5\n|weight-lbs2=121.3\n|weight-kg2=55.0\n|abilitylayout=2+2\n|ability1=Sand Veil\n|abilityd=Sand Rush\n|abilitydcaption=Sandslash\n|ability2-1=Snow Cloak\n|abilityd2=Slush Rush\n|abilityd2caption=Alolan Sandslash\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|expyield=158\n|oldexp=163\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Yellow\n|formcolors=yes\n|catchrate=90\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=sandslash\n|generation=1\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Sandslash\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'サンドパン\'\'\' \'\'Sandpan\'\') is a {{type|Ground}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation I]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s from {{p|Sandshrew}} starting at [[level]] 22.\n\nIn [[Alola]], Sandslash has a [[regional variant]] that is {{2t|Ice|Steel}}. It evolves from Alolan Sandshrew when exposed to an [[Ice Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\nSandslash is a bipedal, ground dwelling {{wp|pangolin|pholidote}} Pokémon. Although Sandslash is usually bipedal, it can run on all fours. Most of its underside is light yellow with a white underbelly. It has a narrow muzzle, almond-shaped blue eyes, and a thick tail. Its back is mostly covered in sharp, brown quills formed from its tough, dry hide. It has two large claws on its paws and feet. These claws are its primary weapons and are used for slashing, but can also be used for burrowing. Its claws and spikes can both break off and are shed regularly, but grow back quickly. It can curl into a large ball, which allows it to roll to attack or escape, protect itself from heatstroke, and guard its belly. Sandslash is also adept at climbing trees and is prone to ambush its enemies from above. Sandslash can mostly be found in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Rough-terrain Pokémon|deserts}}.\n\nIn the Alola region, Sandslash has an icy blue hide and quills covered in ice. These quills stand taller than a regular Sandslash\'s quills and resemble icicles. This Pokémon uses its hide for camouflage in the snow, while leaving only its spines exposed. Its body emmits cold air, which sharpens its quills. Its forepaws are larger than its counterpart, and its claws are longer, thinner, and hooked at the tips. Formerly used for climbing trees, they now allow it scale an iceberg. Despite the weight of its ice-covered body, Alolan Sandslash is able to move swiftly by carving a path in the snow with its claws. This Pokémon tends to live in the deeper parts of snowy mountains, where climbing is forbidden. However, the sprays of snow it kicks up are popular shots for photographers.<ref>[http://www.pokemon-sunmoon.com/en-us/pokemon/alolan-sandslash/ Pokémon Sun and Moon site | Alolan Sandslash]</ref>\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Jenaro Sandslash.png|thumb|left|250px|Sandslash in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:Mount Lanakila Sandslash.png|thumb|250px|Alolan Sandslash in the anime]]\n===In the main series===\n====Major appearances====\nA Sandslash owned by [[Corey]] was one of the Pokémon captured and cloned by {{OBP|Mewtwo|original series}} in \'\'[[M01|Mewtwo Strikes Back]]\'\'. When {{TRT}} saw it being cloned, it was mistaken for its pre-evolution, Sandshrew. The Sandslash clone was seen again in \'\'[[Mewtwo Returns]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[EP141|Good \'Quil Hunting]]\'\', [[Koji]] informed {{Ash}} about a place that was good for catching {{p|Cyndaquil}}. After Ash captured a Cyndaquil, the Trainer challenged Ash to a 1-on-1 [[Pokémon battle]] to determine who would keep the Cyndaquil. Koji used a Sandslash against [[Ash\'s Cyndaquil]] and lost.\n\nThree Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP225|Bulbasaur... the Ambassador!]]\'\', where they helped dig a new lake for the {{type|Grass}} Pokémon at [[Professor Oak\'s Laboratory]].\n\nIn \'\'[[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Time & Darkness]]\'\', Sandslash was a member of Team Razor Wind, along with {{p|Scyther}} and {{p|Zangoose}}. The trio of clawed Pokémon were first seen being blasted out of [[Wigglytuff\'s Guild]]. Team Razor Wind overheard that [[Team Poképals]] were assigned with the task of traveling to the Labyrinth Cave to get a {{p|Gabite}} Scale for an ailing {{p|Shinx}}, and decided to attempt beating [[Team Poképals]]. Unfortunately for Team Razor Wind, Gabite beat them up. It reappeared alongside its team in \'\'[[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky - Beyond Time & Darkness]]\'\'.\n\nAlolan Sandslash debuted in \'\'[[SM080|Not Caving Under Pressure!]]\'\', where it evolved from an Alolan Sandshrew after touching an [[Ice Stone]]. It gave {{an|Lillie}} an [[Icium Z]] as thanks for helping it battle a {{p|Tyranitar}} that was threatening a home it shared with several other Alolan Sandshrew at [[Mount Lanakila]].\n\n====Minor appearances====\nMultiple Sandslash debuted in \'\'[[EP033|The Flame Pokémon-athon!]]\'\', where they were seen at the Laramie Ranch. One was later seen among the Pokémon participating in the [[Big P Pokémon Race]].\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP047|A Chansey Operation]]\'\' as one of the injured Pokémon brought to the clinic.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[PK01|Pikachu\'s Vacation]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Theme Park]].\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP071|To Master the Onixpected]]\'\'. It was stuck between the rocky body segments of [[Bruno\'s Onix|a giant Onix]] and causing so much pain that the Rock Snake Pokémon rampaged until [[Bruno]] freed it.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP075|Round One - Begin!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Trainer}} competing in the [[Indigo Plateau Conference]].\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[M02|The Power of One]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[PK04|Pikachu\'s Rescue Adventure]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP108|Pokémon Double Trouble]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP146|Tricks of the Trade]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Swap Meet]] in [[Palmpona]].\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP204|Right On, Rhydon!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Pietra]]. She uses it for her digging project.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[M04|Celebi: The Voice of the Forest]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[EP219|Hi Ho Silver...Away!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Jenaro]].\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[The Legend of Thunder!]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in [[Nurse Joy]]\'s poem in \'\'[[EP245|Will the Real Oak Please Stand Up?]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[AG023|Gone Corphishin\']]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash made a brief cameo in \'\'[[M07|Destiny Deoxys]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash made a cameo in \'\'[[AG135|Numero Uno Articuno]]\'\', under the ownership of {{FB|Factory Head|Noland}}. It was among the Pokémon residing at the {{gdis|Battle Factory|III}}.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M08|Lucario and the Mystery of Mew]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[DP008|Gymbaliar!]]\'\', under the ownership of a male Trainer. It was used to battle a {{pkmn2|wild}} {{TP|Brock|Croagunk}} under Jessie\'s command.\n\nA Sandslash made a brief cameo in \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Sandslash made a cameo in \'\'[[M12|Arceus and the Jewel of Life]]\'\'.\n\nA group of Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[DP140|Historical Mystery Tour!]]\'\'. They were among the Pokémon {{an|Barry}} encountered in [[Xatu\'s Forest]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[BW103|Curtain Up, Unova League!]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\' as a resident of [[Allearth Forest]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\', during a flashback.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[M21|The Power of Us]]\'\', where it participated in the effort to put out a fire.\n\nAn Alolan Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[SM125|A Timeless Encounter!]]\'\', under the ownership of an {{tc|Ace Trainer}}. It battled [[Hala]] and his {{p|Makuhita}} in a flashback, but was defeated.\n\nA Trainer\'s Alolan Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[SM129|Battle Royal 151!]]\'\', where it competed in the [[Battle Royal]] preliminary round of the [[Manalo Conference]] but was defeated by {{TP|Kiawe|Turtonator}}.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Kanto}}\n{{Animedexbody|EP071|Sandslash|Ash\'s Pokédex|Sandslash, the Mouse Pokémon. The evolved form of {{p|Sandshrew}}. It attacks opponents with the quills on its back.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|original|Kanto}}\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP008|Sandslash|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Sandslash, the Mouse Pokémon. When it runs at full speed, it sends up a thick cloud of sand in order to hide itself.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n[[File:Sandshrew Sandslash PO.png|thumb|250px|Sandslash in [[Pokémon Origins]]]]\n\n===In Pokémon Origins===\nA Sandslash appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PO02|File 2: Cubone]]\'\'.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Giovanni Sandslash PM.png|thumb|150px|Sandslash in [[Pokémon Pocket Monsters]]]]\n===In the Ash & Pikachu manga===\nSimilar to her anime counterpart, [[Pietra]] owns a Sandslash. It appeared in \'\'[[SP10|The Grand Rhydon Plan]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nSandslash debuted in \'\'[[PS043|Sea Sea Seadra]]\'\', where it and a {{pkmn2|wild}} {{p|Weezing}} appeared behind [[Bill]], still showing the ecology in [[Viridian Forest]] hasn\'t changed back to normal in two years.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS119|A Flaaffy Kerfuffle]]\'\', a Sandslash appeared as one of the Pokémon in {{adv|Professor Oak}}\'s fantasy when he explains that {{pkmn|Trainer}}s should only have six Pokémon with them.\n\nSandslash\'s most predominant appearance was in \'\'[[PS145|Sandslash Surprise]]\'\'. While trying to find out their location, {{adv|Gold}} and {{adv|Silver}} are attacked by a swarm of spiky balls, which are revealed to be Sandslash fleeing from the wrath of {{p|Lugia}}.\n\nA Sandslash was seen as one of the Pokémon used by [[Team Magma]], which first appeared in \'\'[[PS219|What Would You Do for a Whismur?]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in \'\'[[PAXY30|Pinsir Changes]]\'\'.\n\nA Sandslash appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PAXY34|Charizard Transforms]]\'\'.\n\nTwo [[Regional variant|Alolan]] Sandslash debuted in the {{chap|Sun, Moon, Ultra Sun & Ultra Moon}}<!--[[PASM32]]-->, where it was seen on [[Mount Lanakila]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\n{{OBP|Giovanni|Pocket Monsters}} used Sandslash in his hair salon.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Sandslash (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Time and Explorers of Darkness]]: Sandslash is one of the members of Team Razor Wind.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n====Sandslash====\n{{Dex/Header|type=Ground}}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=I|reg1=Kanto|num1=028}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Red|v2=Blue|t2=FFF|entry=Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Yellow|entry=It is skilled at slashing enemies with its claws. If broken, they start to grow back in a day.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Stadium|t=FFF|color=000|entry=Curls into a ball of sharp spikes and rolls into enemies. It is also adept at slashing with its sharp claws.}}\n|}\n