Alolan Sandslash and its Alolan {{p|Sandshrew|pre-evolution}}.\n* In the [[Pokémon Red and Green beta|Pokémon Red and Blue beta]], Sandslash\'s original name was "Sandstorm".\n* Sandslash and its {{p|Sandshrew|pre-evolution}} share their {{pkmn|category}} with {{p|Rattata}}, {{p|Raticate}}, {{p|Pikachu}}, and {{p|Raichu}}. They are all known as the Mouse Pokémon, though Rattata and Raticate have also been called the Rat Pokémon.\n** They all have at least one family member with a [[regional variant]] in Alola.\n\n===Origin===\n{{bulbanews|On the Origin of Species: Sandshrew and Sandslash}}\nSandslash shares various physical traits with the {{wp|pangolin}}. It also draws from {{wp|hedgehog}}s, {{wp|porcupine}}s, and {{wp|echidna}}s due to its coloration and having spikes instead of scales. Both Sandshrew and Sandslash are mentioned to have poisonous claws, similar to how some species of the {{wp|shrew}} are poisonous.\n\n====Name origin====\nSandslash is a combination of \'\'sand\'\' and \'\'slash\'\', referring to its long claws.\n\nSandpan may be a combination of \'\'sand\'\' and \'\'{{wp|pangolin}}\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ground|type2=Ground\n|ja=サンドパン \'\'Sandpan\'\'|jameaning=From "sand" and "pangolin"\n|fr=Sablaireau|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|sable|sand}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|blaireau|badger}}\'\'\n|es=Sandslash|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Sandamer|demeaning=From \'\'Sand\'\'\n|it=Sandslash|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=고지 \'\'Koji\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|고슴도치 \'\'goseumdochi\'\'|hedgehog}} and {{tt|두더지 \'\'dudeoji\'\'|mole}}\n|zh_yue=穿山王 \'\'Chyūnsāanwòhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=A portmanteau of {{wp|Pangolin|{{tt|穿山甲|pangolin}}}} and {{tt|王|king}}. Literally "King of going through mountains"\n|zh_cmn=穿山王 \'\'Chuānshānwáng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=A portmanteau of {{wp|Pangolin|{{tt|穿山甲|pangolin}}}} and {{tt|王|king}}. Literally "King of going through mountains"\n|he=סנדסלאש \'\'Sendslash\'\'|hemeaning=Transcription of English name\n|